  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACT Haiyan follow-on appeal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihoods
Outputs 1: Target fisher folk and farmer households have implemented livelihood diversification
- Procure and distribute capital inputs for primary livelihoods
- Assess the organizational capacity of existing CBOs
- Conduct training and mentoring of CBOs based on their capacity building plans
- Conduct consultation with City Disaster Risk Reduction Management Council

WASH: 
Output 1: Affected households have built/ reparied latrines
- Affected households have received hygiene kits
Output 2: Affected households have received hygiene kits
- Distribution of hygiene kits and water storage materials
Output 3: Local officials facilitate community awareness sessions on participatory disaster risk and vulnerability assessment, sanitation and hygiene
- Conduct training of trainers for local officials
Output 4: Affected households are oriented and trained on household disaster risk reduction and mitigation and sanitation and hygiene
- Development and distribution of WASH promotional materials</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a one-year follow-on to the ACT Typhoon Haiyan response. There are three interventions: WASH, livelihoods, and Q&amp;amp;A, all in Ormoc City, Leyte, Philippines.

Livelihoods
Goal: Beneficiaries recover and rebuild their livelihoods in ways to maximize their resilience to future disasters

Outcome 1: Disaster-affected small-scale fisher folk and farmer households in Ormoc City barangays have increased livelihood diversification and productivity from primary livelihoods to improve resilience to shocks and stresses

WASH
Goal: Typhoon-affected families of Brgy Linao, Bantigue and Ipil have improved community and household sanitation and hygiene practices, and solid waste management.

Outcome 1: Households affected by typhoon Haiyan have increased their resilience to potential future hazards through improved sanitation, hygiene and solid waste management.</narrative>
  </description>
